{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.04 Judges 1.04.010 1.04.020 1.04.030 1.04.040 1.04.050 1.04.060", "num": "1.04", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.04", "title": "Chapter 1.04 Judges", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.04.010 Any person over the age of 30 who is generally knowledgeable in the laws applicable upon the Bad River Reservation shall be eligible for appointment as judge. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.04.010 was formerly codified as 104.1", "num": "1.04.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.04|1.04.010", "title": "1.04.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.04.020 Any judge of the Bad River Tribal Court may be suspended, dismissed, or removed after written notice and fair hearing in executive session, by a two thirds vote of the Tribal Council for just cause. Each judge shall be appointed for a term of six (6) years, unless sooner removed for cause, or unless elected to the Tribal Council, and shall be eligible for reappointment. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.04.020 was formerly codified as 104.2", "num": "1.04.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.04|1.04.020", "title": "1.04.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.04.030 No individual shall serve as judge while serving as a member of the Tribal Council or as a tribal law enforcement officer. The duties of any judge who is nominated for election to the Tribal Council shall be transferred to other judges of the court pending the election. If the judge shall be elected to the Tribal Council, his term of judge shall terminate at 12:01 midnight the day prior to the commencement of his term on the Tribal Council. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.04.030 was formerly codified as 104.3", "num": "1.04.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.04|1.04.030", "title": "1.04.030", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.04.040 No judge shall be qualified to act in any case wherein he or she has any direct interest. A tribal judge shall not, unless his service is agreeable with all parties, sit on any case wherein his or her spouse, mother, father, sister, brother, son, daughter, grandfather, or grandmother, is a party. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.04.040 was formerly codified as 104.4", "num": "1.04.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.04|1.04.040", "title": "1.04.040", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.04.050 In case of a vacancy, the judgeship will be filled by an appointment through a majority vote of the Bad River Tribal Council. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.04.050 was formerly codified as 104.5", "num": "1.04.050", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.04|1.04.050", "title": "1.04.050", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.04.060 It shall be the duty of the court to judge all cases brought before it. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.04.060 was formerly codified as 104.6", "num": "1.04.060", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.04|1.04.060", "title": "1.04.060", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.04.060"}
