{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.05.010 Sessions of the Bad River Tribal Court shall before the chief judge or an associate judge. Prior Codifications \u00a71.05.010 was formerly codified as 105.1", "num": "1.05.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.05|1.05.010", "title": "1.05.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.05.020 All actions for violations of Tribal Ordinances shall be brought in the name of the Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Tribe of Chippewa Indians. Prior Codifications \u00a71.05.020 was formerly codified as 105.2", "num": "1.05.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.05|1.05.020", "title": "1.05.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.05.030 Any person appearing as a defendant in a civil case or action in the Bad River Tribal Court shall have the right to be represented by a spokesman or an attorney at his own expense provided that such spokesman or attorney has made proper application to this court for admission to practice before it. Such application procedures shall be established by the Tribal Court. Prior Codifications \u00a71.05.030 was formerly codified as 105.3", "num": "1.05.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.05|1.05.030", "title": "1.05.030", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.05.040 All trials shall be conducted in a manner so as to afford all those who appear before it all rights guaranteed by the Indian Civil Rights Act of 1968, 25 U.S.C. Secs. 1301, 1302, and 1303, as amended. Prior Codifications \u00a71.05.040 was formerly codified as 105.4", "num": "1.05.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.05|1.05.040", "title": "1.05.040", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.05.050 The court in its discretion may assess court costs against a defendant found to have violated a tribal ordinance. Prior Codifications \u00a71.05.050 was formerly codified as 105.5", "num": "1.05.050", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.05|1.05.050", "title": "1.05.050", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.05.060 The court in its discretion may apportion and assess court costs, against the parties to a civil action. In any case in which the court has appointed a guardian ad litem, psychologist or other witness, or ordered a social services study, the costs therefore may be assessed against the parties. Prior Codifications \u00a71.05.060 was formerly codified as 105.6", "num": "1.05.060", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.05|1.05.060", "title": "1.05.060", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.060"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.070", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.05.070 Except as specified herein, all records and files of the Bad River Tribal Court shall be available for public inspection during regular office hours of the Clerk of Court. Prior Codifications \u00a71.05.070 was formerly codified as 105.7", "num": "1.05.070", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.05|1.05.070", "title": "1.05.070", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.070"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.080", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.05.080 All juvenile files shall be closed. The may in its discretion and in the interest of privacy, deem other court files as closed files. All closed files shall be unavailable for public inspection without a court order. Prior Codifications \u00a71.05.080 was formerly codified as 105.8", "num": "1.05.080", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.05|1.05.080", "title": "1.05.080", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.080"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.090", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.05.090 Individuals securing documents from tribal court files or transcripts of tribal court proceedings, if available, shall, unless otherwise ordered by the court, pay the actual cost of reproduction or preparation of such material. Prior Codifications \u00a71.05.090 was formerly codified as 105.9", "num": "1.05.090", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.05|1.05.090", "title": "1.05.090", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.090"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.100", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.05.100 Time (a) In computing any period of time prescribed or allowed by tribal law or by an order of the Tribal Court, the day of the act, event, or default from which the designated period of time begins to run shall not be included. The last day of the period so computed shall be included, unless it is a Saturday, a Sunday, or a tribal holiday. When the period of time to be computed is less than 11 days, Saturdays, Sundays, and tribal holidays shall be excluded in the computation. (b) Whenever a party has the right or is required to do some act or take some proceedings within a prescribed period after service of a notice or other paper upon the party, and the notice or paper is served by mail, three (3) days shall be added to the prescribed period. (c) When an act is required to be done at or within a specified time, the court may order the period enlarged upon motion for cause shown and upon just terms. If the action is made after the expiration of the specified time, it shall not be granted unless the court finds that the failure to act was the result of excusable neglect. Prior Codifications \u00a71.05.100 was formerly codified as 105.10", "num": "1.05.100", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.05|1.05.100", "title": "1.05.100 Time", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.100"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.110", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.05.110 Judicial Rules The Tribal Court may adopt such procedural rules for the operation of Tribal Court and the regulation of the Bad as it deems proper. Prior Codifications \u00a71.05.110 was formerly codified as 105.11", "num": "1.05.110", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.05|1.05.110", "title": "1.05.110 Judicial Rules", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.05.110"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.06", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.06 Jurisdiction 1.06.010", "num": "1.06", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.06", "title": "Chapter 1.06 Jurisdiction", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.06"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.06.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.06.010 (a) The Bad River Tribal Court shall have jurisdiction over all matters in the following categories: (1) All actions arising between persons situated on the Bad River Reservation in relation to property or events upon the reservation. (2) All actions arising out of events or occurrences on the Bad River Reservation, regardless of whether the individuals who are parties thereto reside on or off the reservation or are members or non-members of the Tribe. (3) All alleged violations of ordinances duly in effect upon the Bad River Reservation whether the alleged violator is a member or non-member of the Bad River Band or resides on or off the Bad River Reservation. (4) All alleged violations of ordinances duly in effect pertaining to hunting, fishing, trapping or gathering by members in the territory described in Article I, Section 2 of the Bad River Constitution . (5) Any other case otherwise provided by tribal ordinance. (b) If any court of competent jurisdiction determines that the Tribal Court cannot lawfully assert jurisdiction over any class of individuals or claims as described in para. (a), above, the assertion of jurisdiction over all remaining classes of individuals or claims shall not be effected thereto. Prior Codifications \u00a71.06.010 was formerly codified as 106.1", "num": "1.06.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.06|1.06.010", "title": "1.06.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.06.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.07", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.07 Clerk of Court 1.07.010 1.07.020 1.07.030", "num": "1.07", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.07", "title": "Chapter 1.07 Clerk of Court", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.07"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.07.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.07.010 The Bad River Tribal Council shall appoint a Clerk of Court for the Tribal Court. The Clerk shall render assistance to the court, to the enforcement personnel, and to all persons having business with the court. It shall further be the duty of the Clerk to attend and keep a written record of all proceedings of the court, to administer oaths to witnesses, to receive the transcript of cases and other papers on appeal and make a permanent record properly filed, to collect all penalties, forfeitures and other receipts and to pay out fees authorized by court and Tribal ordinances. The Clerk shall make periodic accountings to the Tribal Council and to the Tribal Court of all funds received and disbursed. Such accounting shall be made at least quarterly, and upon request by either the Tribal Council or the Tribal Court. Prior Codifications \u00a71.07.010 was formerly codified as 107.1", "num": "1.07.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.07|1.07.010", "title": "1.07.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.07.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.07.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.07.020 The salary and term of office of the Clerk of Court shall be determined by the Tribal Council. Prior Codifications \u00a71.07.020 was formerly codified as 107.2", "num": "1.07.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.07|1.07.020", "title": "1.07.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.07.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.07.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.07.030 The Clerk of Court shall also serve as the Clerk of the Court of Appeals. Prior Codifications \u00a71.07.030 was formerly codified as 107.3", "num": "1.07.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.07|1.07.030", "title": "1.07.030", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.07.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.08", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.08 Prosecutor 1.08.010 1.08.020", "num": "1.08", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.08", "title": "Chapter 1.08 Prosecutor", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.08"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.08.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.08.010 One or more persons shall be appointed by the Tribal Council to serve as prosecutor or prosecutors for such term and for such compensation as shall be specified. Unless otherwise specified the Tribal Attorney shall be deemed appointed prosecutor. Prior Codifications \u00a71.08.010 was formerly codified as 108.1", "num": "1.08.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.08|1.08.010", "title": "1.08.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.08.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.08.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.08.020 Prosecutors shall receive complaints from members and non-members and shall have the power to file complaints on his or her own authority. It shall be the responsibility of the prosecutor to present cases on behalf of the Tribe to the Tribal Court, but a prosecutor shall present only those cases in which he or she finds, upon investigation, that there is reasonable justification for the complaint. Prior Codifications \u00a71.08.020 was formerly codified as 108.2", "num": "1.08.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.08|1.08.020", "title": "1.08.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.08.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.09", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.09 Court Records 1.09.010", "num": "1.09", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.09", "title": "Chapter 1.09 Court Records", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.09"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.09.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.09.010 The Tribal Court shall keep a record of proceedings of the court, which record shall reflect the title of the case, the names of the parties, the name of the judge assigned, the substance of the complaint, the date, the nature and appearances at all proceedings, the findings, conclusions, and judgment of the court, together with any other facts or circumstances deemed pertinent to the case. Prior Codifications \u00a71.09.010 was formerly codified as 109.1", "num": "1.09.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.09|1.09.010", "title": "1.09.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.09.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.10", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.10 Complaints and Answers 1.10.010", "num": "1.10", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.10", "title": "Chapter 1.10 Complaints and Answers", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.10"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.10.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.10.010 (a) No complaint filed in the Tribal Court shall be valid unless it shall bear the signature of the plaintiff, plaintiff's counsel, or complainant. Upon the filing of the complaint, the Clerk shall issue a summons to which shall be attached a copy of the complaint directing the defendant to appear before the court to answer the complaint at the time and place specified. Any summons in a civil case, other than an action filed by the Tribe for violation of an ordinance, and seeking either damages or injunctive relief, or both, shall require that a written answer be served on the complainant and the court within not more than thirty (30) days from the date of service of the summons and copy of complaint. (b) At the time and place, and in the manner properly specified by the summons, the defendant shall answer the complaint. Such answer, in the case of an action filed by the Tribe for the violation of an ordinance shall admit or deny the charge, or the defendant shall stand mute or plead no contest. In all other cases the answer shall admit or deny each of the allegations of the complaint, and shall assert any grounds for dismissal, any permitted affirmative defense, any counter claims, and any third-party claims. (c) Any case charging a defendant with violation of a tribal conservation ordinance may be commenced by filing of a citation containing the time, date, and place of the alleged violation, the name (if known) of the alleged violator, the date of birth and address (if known) of the alleged violator, the section alleged to have been violated, a brief summary statement of the facts constituting the violation, a notification to the alleged violator of the date he or she is required to appear in Tribal Court, and the sworn signature and date of issuing officer. (d) Any other type of case may be commenced as otherwise provided for by ordinance. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.10.010 was formerly codified as 110.1", "num": "1.10.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.10|1.10.010", "title": "1.10.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.10.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.11", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.11 Service 1.11.010 1.11.020 1.11.030 1.11.040 1.11.050", "num": "1.11", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.11", "title": "Chapter 1.11 Service", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.11"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.11.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.11.010 A summons and complaint shall, whenever possible, be served on a defendant by personal service. Personal service shall consist of delivery of the summons and complaint to the defendant in person or to any person of apparent normal understanding residing within the residence of the defendant. Any person over eighteen (18) years of age, not a party to the action, may make personal service. In the case of personal service, an affidavit of service shall be returned to the Clerk and filed in the docket and shall constitute proof of personal service. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.11.010 was formerly codified as 111.1", "num": "1.11.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.11|1.11.010", "title": "1.11.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.11.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.11.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.11.020 When the summons and complaint cannot by reasonable diligence be personally served on the defendant in the manner specified in Article XI, Section 1, service may be made either by mail or publication. In the case of service by mail, true copies of the summons and complaint shall be sent by registered or certified mail to the defendant's last known address. A return receipt for mail delivery signed by the defendant shall be returned to the Clerk and filed in the docket and shall constitute proof of service by mail. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.11.020 was formerly codified as 111.2", "num": "1.11.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.11|1.11.020", "title": "1.11.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.11.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.11.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.11.030 In the event the defendant cannot be served with summons and complaint either personally or by mail in accordance with sections 111.1 or 111.2, service may be made by publication. Service by publication shall mean publication of the summons once in each of two consecutive weeks in a newspaper of general circulation whose readership is primarily located in the vicinity of the Bad River Reservation. The published summons shall state the address at which the complaint may be obtained. Proof of publication of the summons shall be returned to the Clerk and filed in the docket and shall constitute proof of service by publication. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.11.030 was formerly codified as 111.3", "num": "1.11.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.11|1.11.030", "title": "1.11.030", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.11.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.11.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.11.040 Service of all papers filed in action subsequent to the summons and complaint may be in person or by first class mail. The filing of a paper with the court is the filer's certificate that a copy thereof has been properly served on the other parties. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.11.040 was formerly codified as 111.4", "num": "1.11.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.11|1.11.040", "title": "1.11.040", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.11.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.11.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.11.050 The court may provide notice to any party appearing in open court of any subsequent proceeding by orally so informing the party in which case the minutes shall reflect such notice or by causing written notice to be hard served upon the party in open court. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.11.050 was formerly codified as 111.5", "num": "1.11.050", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.11|1.11.050", "title": "1.11.050", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.11.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.12", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.12 Judgment 1.12.010 1.12.020 1.12.030", "num": "1.12", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.12", "title": "Chapter 1.12 Judgment", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.12"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.12.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.12.010 All judgments shall be ordered in writing. All judgments shall be accompanied by findings of fact and conclusions of law which shall be made in writing or on the record in open court. Prior Codifications \u00a71.12.010 was formerly codified as 112.1", "num": "1.12.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.12|1.12.010", "title": "1.12.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.12.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.12.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.12.020 Upon failure of a defendant to appear at the time stated in the summons, the plaintiff may proceed to offer evidence including proof that the defendant was served with summons and the court may render a judgment granting such relief as the evidence warrants, provided that the defaulting party may apply in writing to reopen the case within twenty (20) days of a default judgment upon showing good cause for his failure to answer the summons. Upon failure of the plaintiff without just cause to appear at the time set by the summons for hearing, the court may dismiss the action with or without prejudice. Prior Codifications \u00a71.12.020 was formerly codified as 112.2", "num": "1.12.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.12|1.12.020", "title": "1.12.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.12.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.12.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.12.030 In addition to, or in lieu of, a penalty or forfeiture provided for violation of a tribal ordinance, the Court may order any defendant found to have violated a tribal ordinance to perform community service a specified nature and duration. The number of hours of community service ordered by the court may not exceed the maximum penalty or forfeiture provided for the violation divided by the current federal minimum wage. Prior Codifications \u00a71.12.030 was formerly codified as 112.3", "num": "1.12.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.12|1.12.030", "title": "1.12.030", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.12.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.13", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.13 Initial Appearance 1.13.010 1.13.020 1.13.030 1.13.040", "num": "1.13", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.13", "title": "Chapter 1.13 Initial Appearance", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.13"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.13.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.13.010 This chapter applies to initial appearance in civil actions brought by the Tribe of violations of ordinances. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.13.010 was formerly codified as 113.1", "num": "1.13.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.13|1.13.010", "title": "1.13.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.13.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.13.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.13.020 At the initial appearance the judge shall read to the defendant the charge against him or her and inform him or her of the maximum forfeiture and other penalties that can be imposed. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.13.020 was formerly codified as 113.2", "num": "1.13.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.13|1.13.020", "title": "1.13.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.13.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.13.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.13.030 The judge shall inform the defendant of the following rights: (a) To be represented by counsel at his or her own expense. (b) To admit or deny the charges to stand mute, or plead to no contest. (c) That he or she has the right to a trial before the court. (d) To subpoena witnesses. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.13.030 was formerly codified as 113.3", "num": "1.13.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.13|1.13.030", "title": "1.13.030", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.13.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.13.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.13.040 (a) If the defendant appears unrepresented by counsel and states his or her intent to retain counsel, the court shall adjourn the initial appearance in order to enable defendant to retain counsel. No defendant shall be entitled to more than one adjournment. (b) If the defendant admits the charge, the court shall find him or her guilty. Penalty may be imposed immediately or at a later time set by the court. (c) If the defendant pleads no contest to the court shall find him or her guilty. Penalty may be imposed immediately or at a later time set by the court. (d) If the defendant denies the charge a trial date shall be set. (e) If the defendant stands mute, the court shall enter a denial and set a date for trial. ( 2-6-91-167 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.13.040 was formerly codified as 113.4", "num": "1.13.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.13|1.13.040", "title": "1.13.040", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.13.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.14", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.14 Enforcement of Court Orders 1.14.010 1.14.020 1.14.030 Contempt of Court 1.14.040 Wage Withholding", "num": "1.14", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.14", "title": "Chapter 1.14 Enforcement of Court Orders", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.14"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.14.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.14.010 Any party or the court of its own motion may seek enforcement of any order by any lawful process or through any competent court of any jurisdiction. Prior Codifications \u00a71.14.010 was formerly codified as 114.1", "num": "1.14.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.14|1.14.010", "title": "1.14.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.14.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.14.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.14.020 (a) For failure of any defendant to pay a forfeiture or any ordered costs in any hunting or fishing, trapping, or gathering action, the court may order suspensions of any of the defendant's hunting, fishing, trapping or gathering rights until such forfeiture or costs are paid. (b) Such suspension shall be effected by the Clerk of Court, without further order of the court, if the defendant was advised in open court of the date upon which final payment was due and that the specific suspension ordered would follow nonpayment. (c) If the defendant was not so advised in open court, the court shall schedule and notice a hearing at which defendant shall be ordered to show cause why suspension should not be ordered. After such hearing, or upon defendant's failure to appear at such hearing, the court may order the suspension. (d) All forfeitures not paid. When due shall accrue interest at the rate of 1\u00ab&lt; percent per month on the unpaid balance, the first month's interest to be due on the day following the initial due date, and each subsequent month's interest accruing on the same day of each month thereafter. Prior Codifications \u00a71.14.020 was formerly codified as 114.2", "num": "1.14.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.14|1.14.020", "title": "1.14.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.14.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.14.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.14.030 Contempt of Court (a) \"Contempt of Court\" means intentional: (b) The Tribal Court may impose a sanction for contempt of court. (1) Misconduct in the presence of the court which interferes with a court proceeding or with the administration of justice, or which impairs the respect due the court; (2) Disobedience, resistance or obstruction of the authority, process or order of a court; (3) Refusal as a witness to appear, be sworn or answer a question. (c) Procedure (1) A party aggrieved by a contempt of court may move for, or the court on its own motion may impose a contempt sanction. The court, after notice and hearing may impose sanction. (2) The judge presiding in an action may impose a sanction upon a person who commits a contempt of court in the open court. The judge shall impose the sanction immediately after the contempt of court and only for the purpose of preserving order in the court and protecting the authority and dignity of the court. (3) A court may impose one or more of the following sanctions. (A) Payment of a sum of money sufficient to compensate a party for a loss or injury suffered by the party as a result of the contempt of court. (B) A forfeiture not to exceed $1,000 for each day the contempt of court continues. (C) An ordered designed to ensure compliance with a prior order of the court. (D) If the contempt arises in an action involving the exercise of off-reservation hunting, fishing, trapping, or gathering rights, a suspension of any such right. (E) A sanction other than those specified in par. (A) through (D) if the court expressly finds that those sanctions would ineffectual to terminate a continuing contempt of court. Prior Codifications \u00a71.14.030 was formerly codified as 114.3", "num": "1.14.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.14|1.14.030", "title": "1.14.030 Contempt of Court", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.14.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.14.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.14.040 Wage Withholding (a) For any monetary obligation incurred by virtue of any order of the court the court may order the obligator's employer, or any person owing the any money, to withhold from the amount owing to the obligator an amount certain, or a percentage of the amount owed to the obligator, and to submit it to the Clerk of Court who shall disburse it to the person to whom due under the court order. (b) Any person ordered to make a withholding under this section may subtract and retain from other funds due the obligator other sum of $3.00 for each withholding made. (c) Exempt from wage withholding shall be, for each one week period, 30 times the current minimum wage plus $20.00 for each dependent. Prior Codifications \u00a71.14.040 was formerly codified as 114.4", "num": "1.14.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.14|1.14.040", "title": "1.14.040 Wage Withholding", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.14.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.15", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.15 Subpoenas 1.15.010 1.15.020 1.15.030 1.15.040", "num": "1.15", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.15", "title": "Chapter 1.15 Subpoenas", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.15"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.15.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.15.010 The judges of the Tribal Court shall have the power to issue subpoenas for the attendance of witnesses and/or production of documents or physical evidence on the request of any party to an action or on the court's own initiative, which subpoena shall bear the signature of the judge issuing it. Service of subpoenas shall be by any person not a party at least 18 years of age. Prior Codifications \u00a71.15.010 was formerly codified as 115.1", "num": "1.15.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.15|1.15.010", "title": "1.15.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.15.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.15.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.15.020 Service of subpoena shall be made by delivering a copy of it to the person named or by leaving a copy at his place of residence with any competent person sixteen (16) years of age or older who also resides there. Prior Codifications \u00a71.15.020 was formerly codified as 115.2", "num": "1.15.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.15|1.15.020", "title": "1.15.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.15.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.15.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.15.030 Proof of service of the subpoena shall be filed with the clerk of court by noting on the back of a copy of the subpoena the date, time and place that it was served and noting the name of the person to whom it was delivered. Proof of service shall be signed by the person who actually served the subpoena. Prior Codifications \u00a71.15.030 was formerly codified as 115.3", "num": "1.15.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.15|1.15.030", "title": "1.15.030", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.15.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.15.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.15.040 In the absence of justification satisfactory to the court, a person who fails to obey a subpoena may be deemed to be in contempt of court. Prior Codifications \u00a71.15.040 was formerly codified as 115.4", "num": "1.15.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.15|1.15.040", "title": "1.15.040", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.15.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.16 Criminal Procedure Subchapter A Search Warrants \u00a7\u00a7 1.16.010 \u2013 1.16.060 Subchapter B Arrest \u00a7\u00a7 1.16.070 \u2013 1.16.070 Subchapter C Arrest Warrants \u00a7\u00a7 1.16.080 \u2013 1.16.100 Subchapter D Arraignment \u00a7\u00a7 1.16.110 \u2013 1.16.160 Subchapter E Bail \u00a7\u00a7 1.16.170 \u2013 1.16.190 Subchapter F Notification of Rights at Time of Arrest \u00a7\u00a7 1.16.200 \u2013 1.16.200", "num": "1.16", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16", "title": "Chapter 1.16 Criminal Procedure", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16/A", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Subchapter A Search Warrants 1.16.010 1.16.020 1.16.030 1.16.040 1.16.050 1.16.060", "num": "A", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|A", "title": "Subchapter A Search Warrants", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16/A"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.010 Every tribal judge shall have the power to issue warrants for the search and seizure of property and premises of any person under the jurisdiction of the court. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.010 was formerly codified as 116.1", "num": "1.16.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|A|1.16.010", "title": "1.16.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.020 No warrant for search and seizure shall be valid unless it contains the name or description of the person or property to be searched and describes the articles or property to be seized and bears the signature of a duly qualified judge of the Bad River Tribal Court. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.020 was formerly codified as 116.2", "num": "1.16.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|A|1.16.020", "title": "1.16.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.030 No warrant of search and seizure shall be issued except upon probable cause that a search will discover: stolen, embezzled, contraband, or otherwise criminally possessed property which constitutes evidence of the commission of a criminal offense. Such probable cause shall be supported by a written and sworn statement based upon reliable information. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.030 was formerly codified as 116.3", "num": "1.16.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|A|1.16.030", "title": "1.16.030", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.040 Warrants of search and seizure shall be executed by authorized tribal enforcement personnel. The warrant shall be returned within the time limit shown on the face of the warrant, which in no case shall be longer than three (3) days from the date of issuance. Warrants not returned within such time limit shall be void. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.040 was formerly codified as 116.4", "num": "1.16.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|A|1.16.040", "title": "1.16.040", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.050 No enforcement official conduct any search without a valid warrant unless (a) Incident to making a lawful arrest; or (b) With the knowing, voluntary consent of the person being searched; or (c) When he has probable cause to believe that the person searched may be armed and dangerous, and then only to the extent necessary to detect the presence of a weapon; (d) When the search is of a motor vehicle capable of being driven away before a warrant can be obtained, and the officer has probable cause to believe that it contains contraband, stolen or embezzled property. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.050 was formerly codified as 116.5", "num": "1.16.050", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|A|1.16.050", "title": "1.16.050", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.060 Anyone interfering with the execution of a search warrant may be found in contempt of court. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.060 was formerly codified as 116.6", "num": "1.16.060", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|A|1.16.060", "title": "1.16.060", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.060"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16/B", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Subchapter B Arrest 1.16.070", "num": "B", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|B", "title": "Subchapter B Arrest", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16/B"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.070", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.070 No tribal enforcement officer shall arrest any person for any offense set out in the Tribal ordinances except when: (a) The officer shall have a warrant signed by a tribal judge commanding the arrest of such person; or (b) The criminal offense shall occur in the presence of the arresting officer; or (c) The officer shall have probable cause to believe that the person to be arrested has committed a criminal offense. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.070 was formerly codified as 116.7", "num": "1.16.070", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|B|1.16.070", "title": "1.16.070", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.070"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16/C", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Subchapter C Arrest Warrants 1.16.080 1.16.090 1.16.100", "num": "C", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|C", "title": "Subchapter C Arrest Warrants", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16/C"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.080", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.080 Every judge of the Bad River Tribal Court shall have the authority to issue warrants to arrest and such warrants shall be issued, the at the discretion of the court, only after a written complaint shall have been filed. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.080 was formerly codified as 116.8", "num": "1.16.080", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|C|1.16.080", "title": "1.16.080", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.080"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.090", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.090 The arrest warrant shall contain the following information: (a) Name or description and address, if known, of the person to be arrested. (b) Date of issuance of the warrant. (c) Description of the offense charged. (d) Signature of the issuing judge. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.090 was formerly codified as 116.9", "num": "1.16.090", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|C|1.16.090", "title": "1.16.090", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.090"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.100", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.100 Law enforcement officials shall be empowered to seek the cooperation of other agencies outside the reservation to secure the arrest of individuals under tribal arrest warrant. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.100 was formerly codified as 116.10", "num": "1.16.100", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|C|1.16.100", "title": "1.16.100", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.100"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16/D", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Subchapter D Arraignment 1.16.110 1.16.120 1.16.130 1.16.140 1.16.150 1.16.160", "num": "D", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|D", "title": "Subchapter D Arraignment", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16/D"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.110", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.110 Arraignment shall be held in open court without unnecessary delay after the accused is taken into custody and in no instance shall arraignment be later than the next regularly scheduled session of court. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.110 was formerly codified as 116.11", "num": "1.16.110", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|D|1.16.110", "title": "1.16.110", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.110"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.120", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.120 Before an accused is required to plead to any criminal charge, the judge shall: (a) Read to the accused and determine that he understands the complaint and the tribal ordinance which he is charged with violating, including the maximum authorized penalty; and (b) Advise the accused that he has the right to remain silent, to be tried by a jury; and to be represented by counsel at his own expense and that arraignment will be postponed should he desire to consult with counsel. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.120 was formerly codified as 116.12", "num": "1.16.120", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|D|1.16.120", "title": "1.16.120", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.120"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.130", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.130 If the accused pleads \"not guilty\" to the charge, a trial date shall then be set and the judge shall then set the conditions for bail prior to trial. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.130 was formerly codified as 116.13", "num": "1.16.130", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|D|1.16.130", "title": "1.16.130", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.130"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.140", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.140 If the accused pleads \"guilty\" to the charge, the judge shall determine that the plea is made voluntarily and that the accused understands the consequences of the plea. The judge may then impose sentence or defer sentencing for a reasonable time in order to obtain any information he or she deems necessary for the imposition of a just sentence. The accused shall be afforded the opportunity to present any information he deems useful in determining the setting of bail. The court shall then upon consideration of such information and all other facts set bail at an appropriate amount. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.140 was formerly codified as 116.14", "num": "1.16.140", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|D|1.16.140", "title": "1.16.140", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.140"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.150", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.150 If the accused refuses to plead, the judge shall enter a plea of not guilty on his or her behalf. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.150 was formerly codified as 116.15", "num": "1.16.150", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|D|1.16.150", "title": "1.16.150", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.150"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.160", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.160 For purposes of alleged violations by corporate entities, any officer of the corporation may appear on behalf of said corporation. Any arrest warrants on behalf of the corporations are executable against any officer or executive official of said corporation. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.160 was formerly codified as 116.16", "num": "1.16.160", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|D|1.16.160", "title": "1.16.160", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.160"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16/E", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Subchapter E Bail 1.16.170 1.16.180 1.16.190", "num": "E", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|E", "title": "Subchapter E Bail", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16/E"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.170", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.170 A schedule of bail monies shall be established by the Tribal Court and made available to an individual charged with a criminal offense. The Clerk of Court or an enforcement official is authorized to accept bail in such specified amounts and to post this bail. Such bail shall only be accepted from individuals who also produce a signed agreement to appear bearing either his or her signature or mark. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.170 was formerly codified as 116.17", "num": "1.16.170", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|E|1.16.170", "title": "1.16.170", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.170"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.180", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.180 The aforementioned bail schedule shall be utilized by the Clerk of Court and/or law enforcement officials. The Tribal Court itself may set bail in whatever amount it deems appropriate. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.180 was formerly codified as 116.18", "num": "1.16.180", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|E|1.16.180", "title": "1.16.180", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.180"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.190", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.190 Should the Tribal Court feel any of the following will reasonably assure the appearance of the individual at any time lawfully required, the court may impose one or more of the following conditions for release form custody pending trial: (a) Release on personal recognizance upon execution by the accused of a written promise to appear at trial and all other lawfully required times. (b) Release to the custody of a designated person or organization agreeing to assure the accused's appearance. (c) Release with reasonable restrictions on travel, association, or place of residence of the accused during the period of release. (d) Release after deposition by the accused or a bondsman of bond in either cash or other sufficient collateral in an amount specified by the judge or a bail schedule. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.190 was formerly codified as 116.19", "num": "1.16.190", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|E|1.16.190", "title": "1.16.190", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.190"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16/F", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Subchapter F Notification of Rights at Time of Arrest 1.16.200", "num": "F", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|F", "title": "Subchapter F Notification of Rights at Time of Arrest", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16/F"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.200", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.16.200 Upon arrest, the suspect shall be advised of the following rights: (a) The right to remain silent. (b) That any statements made by the suspect may be used against him or her in court. (c) The right to obtain counsel at his or her own expense. Prior Codifications \u00a71.16.200 was formerly codified as 116.20", "num": "1.16.200", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.16|F|1.16.200", "title": "1.16.200", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.16.200"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.17", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.17 Parties to a Violation 1.17.010", "num": "1.17", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.17", "title": "Chapter 1.17 Parties to a Violation", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.17"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.17.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.17.010 Any person who is concerned in the commission of a violation of a tribal ordinance is a principal and may be adjudged to have committed the violation although such person did not directly commit it and although the person who did directly do so has not been subject to an act or in Tribal Court. A person is concerned in the commission of a violation if such person: (a) Directly violates; or (b) Aids and abets the violation; or (c) Is party to a conspiracy with one or more others to violate or advises, hires, counsels, or otherwise procures another to commit the violation. Prior Codifications \u00a71.17.010 was formerly codified as 117.1", "num": "1.17.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.17|1.17.010", "title": "1.17.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.17.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.18", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.18 Juveniles 1.18.010 1.18.020", "num": "1.18", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.18", "title": "Chapter 1.18 Juveniles", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.18"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.18.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.18.010 The class juveniles shall include all individuals who have not achieved their respective eighteenth (18) birthday. Prior Codifications \u00a71.18.010 was formerly codified as 118.1", "num": "1.18.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.18|1.18.010", "title": "1.18.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.18.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.18.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.18.020 Court processing of, and proceedings concerning juveniles shall be as provided in Chapter 1.25 , Bad River Ordinance. Prior Codifications \u00a71.18.020 was formerly codified as 118.2", "num": "1.18.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.18|1.18.020", "title": "1.18.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.18.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.19", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.19 Reserved", "num": "1.19", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.19", "title": "Chapter 1.19 Reserved", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.19"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.20", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.20 Seizures 1.20.010 1.20.020 1.20.030", "num": "1.20", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.20", "title": "Chapter 1.20 Seizures", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.20"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.20.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.20.010 In any case where tribal ordinance authorizes the seizure of any perishable resource or product, the Conservation Department may hold such resource product until the Tribal Court has ruled on its ultimate disposition, or may sell such resource or product if (a) it is not needed as evidence, and (b) it will spoil or lose substantial part of its value if retained until ultimate disposition. Prior Codifications \u00a71.20.010 was formerly codified as 120.1", "num": "1.20.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.20|1.20.010", "title": "1.20.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.20.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.20.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.20.020 If the Conservation Department chooses to sell the resource or product it may do so by auction or privately to a tribal program, and shall retain the proceeds of such sale until ultimate disposition of the case, at which time the proceeds shall be disposed of as the court orders. Prior Codifications \u00a71.20.020 was formerly codified as 120.2", "num": "1.20.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.20|1.20.020", "title": "1.20.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.20.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.20.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.20.030 Under no circumstance where the conservation department had reasonable cause to believe that violation of a tribal ordinance providing for seizure and forfeiture of a resource or product had been committed shall the department be liable for any difference between the proceeds actually received by the conservation department and any amount claimed as the fair market value of the resource or product. Prior Codifications \u00a71.20.030 was formerly codified as 120.3", "num": "1.20.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.20|1.20.030", "title": "1.20.030", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.20.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.21", "_type": "page"}}
