{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.25.300 Child Welfare Committee (a) There is hereby established a Child Welfare Committee, composed of three persons designated by the Tribal Council in executive session who shall establish procedures and guidelines for the conduct of committee business. The child welfare coordinator, tribal attorney, and other staff aides designated by the committee shall serve in advisory capacities to the committee, as requested by the committee. (b) The Child Welfare Committee shall have the authority to meet, consider the conditions of a child alleged to be in need of care, and determine whether a case commenced in another jurisdiction should be transferred to children's court or whether the Tribe should intervene in the proceeding in the other jurisdiction. (c) By this chapter and by the resolution adopting this chapter , the Child Welfare Committee is delegated the Tribal Council's authority under 25 U.S.C. sec. 1915(c) to establish in individual cases a different order of preference than that set forth in 25 U.S.C. sec. 1915 (a) and (b). ( 5-9-95-49 ; 4-5-89-33 ; 3-8-88-128 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.25.300 was formerly codified as 125.27", "num": "1.25.300", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.25|1.25.300", "title": "1.25.300 Child Welfare Committee", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.25.300"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.25.310", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.25.310 Right of Access to Records Any party deemed appropriate by the Court, and the child who has been the subject of the termination of parental rights proceeding, suspension of parental rights proceeding, adoption proceeding or a customary adoption proceeding, has the right, upon reaching the age of majority, to review all the court\u2019s file on these matters subject to redaction of names or the rights of confidentiality or some documents under federal or tribal law. ( 10-14-14-330 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.25.310 was formerly codified as 125.28", "num": "1.25.310", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.25|1.25.310", "title": "1.25.310 Right of Access to Records", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.25.310"}
