{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.32.110 Effect of Divorce, Annulment and Decree of Separation A person who is divorced from a decedent or whose marriage to the decedent has been annulled is not a surviving spouse unless, by virtue of a subsequent remarriage, he or she is married to the decedent at the time of passing. A decree of separation which does not terminate the status of husband and wife is not a divorce for purposes of this Code. Prior Codifications \u00a71.32.110 was formerly codified as 132.11", "num": "1.32.110", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.32|I|1.32.110", "title": "1.32.110 Effect of Divorce, Annulment and Decree of Separation", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.32.110"}
