{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.37.010 Scope These rules shall apply to all proceedings in Tribal Court. The Tribal Court, subject to the decisions of the Court of Appeals, shall interpret and apply these rules. The policies and rationales underlying the Federal Rules of Evidence and the Wisconsin Rules of Evidence may be cited as persuasive authority, but the Federal Rules and Wisconsin Rules shall not be controlling. Prior Codifications \u00a71.37.010 was formerly codified as 150.1", "num": "1.37.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.37|1.37.010", "title": "1.37.010 Scope", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.37.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.37.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.37.020 Rulings on Evidence No appeal may be predicated on an evidentiary ruling unless a substantial right of a party is affected and (a) An objection or motion to strike is timely made, stating the specific ground of objection, unless the specific ground was clear from the context; and (b) In the case of a ruling excluding evidence an offer of proof in the form prescribed by the court is made. Prior Codifications \u00a71.37.020 was formerly codified as 150.2", "num": "1.37.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.37|1.37.020", "title": "1.37.020 Rulings on Evidence", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.37.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.38", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.38 Rules of Evidence; Relevancy 1.38.010 Definitions 1.38.020 Admissibility 1.38.030 Exclusion of Relevant Evidence - General Rule 1.38.040 Exclusion of Relevant Evidence - Specific Rules", "num": "1.38", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.38", "title": "Chapter 1.38 Rules of Evidence; Relevancy", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.38"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.38.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.38.010 Definitions \"Relevant evidence\" is any evidence tending to make the existence of any fact of consequence more or less probable. Prior Codifications \u00a71.38.010 was formerly codified as 151.1", "num": "1.38.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.38|1.38.010", "title": "1.38.010 Definitions", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.38.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.38.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.38.020 Admissibility Only relevant evidence is admissible. Prior Codifications \u00a71.38.020 was formerly codified as 151.2", "num": "1.38.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.38|1.38.020", "title": "1.38.020 Admissibility", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.38.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.38.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.38.030 Exclusion of Relevant Evidence - General Rule Relevant evidence may be excluded if its admission would violate any other section of this chapter , or if its probative value is substantially outweighed by the danger of unfair prejudice, or confusion of the issues, or if it would be cumulative, a waste of time, or cause undue delay. Prior Codifications \u00a71.38.030 was formerly codified as 151.3", "num": "1.38.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.38|1.38.030", "title": "1.38.030 Exclusion of Relevant Evidence - General Rule", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.38.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.38.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.38.040 Exclusion of Relevant Evidence - Specific Rules Evidence of the following is not admissible, even if relevant: (a) Statements made in settlement negotiations or mediation, compromises, or offers to compromise, when offered to prove liability or the lack thereof. (b) Corrective measures taken after an event, which would have made the event less likely to occur, when offered to prove negligence or culpability. (c) Payments, offers to pay, and promises to pay for medical, hospital, or disability expenses, when offered to prove liability. (d) Pleas of no contest or subsequently withdrawn pleas of guilty, in any court, when offered against the person making the plea, to prove liability. (e) Existence of insurance against liability, or lack thereof, when offered to prove negligence or culpability. Prior Codifications \u00a71.38.040 was formerly codified as 151.4", "num": "1.38.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.38|1.38.040", "title": "1.38.040 Exclusion of Relevant Evidence - Specific Rules", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.38.040"}
