{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.43.010 Adjudicative Facts The court may at any time in a proceeding take judicial notice of an adjudicative fact that is not subject to reasonable dispute in that it is either generally known within the territorial jurisdiction of the court or is capable of accurate and ready determination by resort to sources whose accuracy cannot reasonably be questions. Prior Codifications \u00a71.43.010 was formerly codified as 156.1", "num": "1.43.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.43|1.43.010", "title": "1.43.010 Adjudicative Facts", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.43.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.43.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.43.020 Foreign Law The court may take judicial notice of any foreign law properly authenticated. Prior Codifications \u00a71.43.020 was formerly codified as 156.2", "num": "1.43.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.43|1.43.020", "title": "1.43.020 Foreign Law", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.43.020"}
