{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 1.44 Powers of Tribal Wardens 1.44.010 Warrants and Process 1.44.020 Stop and Search 1.44.030 Arrest of Members 1.44.040 Civil Remedial Enforcement", "num": "1.44", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.44", "title": "Chapter 1.44 Powers of Tribal Wardens", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.44"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.44.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.44.010 Warrants and Process Any tribal warden may execute and serve warrants and processes issued by the tribal court in the same manner as any law enforcement officer of the State of Wisconsin may serve and execute such state warrants and processes under state law. ( 6-24-80-85 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.44.010 was formerly codified as 201.1", "num": "1.44.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.44|1.44.010", "title": "1.44.010 Warrants and Process", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.44.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.44.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.44.020 Stop and Search For the purpose of enforcing any natural resource ordinance of the tribe or such other ordinance as the Tribal Council may direct, any tribal warden may stop and board any boat and stop any automobile, snowmobile, or other vehicle, if the tribal warden reasonably suspects there is a violation or breach of such ordinance. Any tribal warden may, with or without warrant, open, enter, and examine all buildings, camps, vessels or boats, wagons, trailers, automobiles or other vehicles snowmobiles, stages, tents, suit cases, valises, packages, and other receptacles and places where the tribal warden has probable cause to believe that game, fish, or other natural products of the Bad River Reservation taken or held in violation or breach of any tribal natural resource ordinance are to be found. ( 6-24-80-85 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.44.020 was formerly codified as 201.2", "num": "1.44.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.44|1.44.020", "title": "1.44.020 Stop and Search", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.44.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.44.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.44.030 Arrest of Members Any tribal warden may arrest, with or without a warrant, any tribal member detected in the actual violation, or whom such warden has probable cause to believe guilty of a violation of any tribal natural resource ordinance or such other tribal ordinance as the Tribal Council may direct, whether such violation is punishable by criminal penalties or civil remedial measures, and may take such member before the tribal court and make proper complaint. ( 6-24-80-85 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.44.030 was formerly codified as 201.3", "num": "1.44.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.44|1.44.030", "title": "1.44.030 Arrest of Members", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.44.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.44.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 1.44.040 Civil Remedial Enforcement Any tribal warden may issue a citation to any member or non-member if the tribal warden reasonably believes that such person has breached a provision of any tribal natural resource ordinance or such other ordinance as the Tribal Council may direct, and may seize and hold any property authorized to be seized in such ordinance, pursuant to the civil remedial forfeiture provisions of the Tribal Court Code. ( 6-24-80-85 .) Prior Codifications \u00a71.44.040 was formerly codified as 201.4", "num": "1.44.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|1|1.44|1.44.040", "title": "1.44.040 Civil Remedial Enforcement", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/1.44.040"}
