{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 3.01 Conservation; General Provision 3.01.010 Waste 3.01.020 Trespass 3.01.030 Tampering with Equipment of Another 3.01.040 Endangered and Threatened Species 3.01.050 Forfeitures", "num": "3.01", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.01", "title": "Chapter 3.01 Conservation; General Provision", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.01"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.01.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.01.010 Waste No member shall unreasonably waste, injure destroy, or impair natural resources while engaging in the exercise of on-reservation hunting, fishing, trapping, or gathering rights, or in the disposition of any animal or plant taken in such exercise, whether such disposition is on-reservation or off-reservation, and whether such waste, injury, destruction or impairment is accomplished by act or by omission. ( 10-3-90-148 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.01.010 was formerly codified as 300.01", "num": "3.01.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.01|3.01.010", "title": "3.01.010 Waste", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.01.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.01.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.01.020 Trespass (a) No member or non-member Indian shall trespass while hunting, fishing, or trapping, snowmobiling, recreational vehicles, or any other activity on land of another, after having been notified by the owner or occupant not to enter or remain on such land. Notification may be personal, either orally or in writing, or by posting. Posting is accomplished if the owner or occupant places a sign at least 11 inches square in at least two conspicuous places for every forty acres to be protected, including the appropriate notice, the name of the person giving notice, and title of \"owner\" or occupant: as appropriate. (b) No non-member shall trespass for the purpose of hunting, fishing, trapping or gathering, snowmobiling, recreational vehicles, or any other activity on lands owned either by the Tribe, a tribal member, or the United States in trust for the Tribe or a tribal member. ( 1-18-91-164 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.01.020 was formerly codified as 300.02", "num": "3.01.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.01|3.01.020", "title": "3.01.020 Trespass", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.01.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.01.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.01.030 Tampering with Equipment of Another No member shall molest, disturb, tamper with or in any way otherwise interfere with any hunting, fishing, trapping or gathering equipment or bait, used, set, or placed by another member without that member's permission. ( 12-5-90-153 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.01.030 was formerly codified as 300.03", "num": "3.01.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.01|3.01.030", "title": "3.01.030 Tampering with Equipment of Another", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.01.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.01.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.01.040 Endangered and Threatened Species No member shall take, transport, possess, process, or sell any plant or animal species contained on either the federal (50 CFR Sections 17.11 and 17.12) or the State of Wisconsin (Wis. Adm. Code NR 27.03) endangered or threatened species list, as may be amended from time to time, or any species which the Tribal Council may declare as endangered or threatened, and no tag as provided for in Chapter 3.06 shall be issued or affixed to the carcass or part thereof of any such species. ( 1-18-91-162 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.01.040 was formerly codified as 300.4", "num": "3.01.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.01|3.01.040", "title": "3.01.040 Endangered and Threatened Species", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.01.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.01.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.01.050 Forfeitures (a) Except as specifically provided in this section, a civil remedial forfeiture not to exceed $1,000 may be assessed against any person for breach of any provision of this chapter . (b) Except as specifically provided in this section, a civil remedial forfeiture not to exceed $2,000 may be assessed against any person for a breach of any provision of this chapter , who has been found to have breached the same provision at least once before in the five years proceeding the violation. (c) In addition to any other penalty herein, the Court may order a suspension or revocation of any or all hunting, fishing and gathering rights. ( 1-18-91-163 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.01.050 was formerly codified as 300.5", "num": "3.01.050", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.01|3.01.050", "title": "3.01.050 Forfeitures", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.01.050"}
