{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.03.020 Definitions (a) \"Conservation Department\" means the Conservation Department of the Tribe. (b) \"Member\" means any person who is enrolled or is eligible for enrollment in the Tribe, or who is recognized as member of the Tribe by the Tribal Council. (c) \"Non-member\" means any person who does not come within the definition of member. (d) \"Reservation\" means the Bad River Reservation. (e) \"To fish\" means to use a hook and line, net, spear, or any other means to catch and take fish. (f) \"Tribal Council\" means the Tribal Council of the Tribe. (g) \"Tribe\" means the Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Tribe of Chippewa Indians of the Bad River Reservation. ( 9-2-81-12 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.03.020 was formerly codified as 302.2", "num": "3.03.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.03|3.03.020", "title": "3.03.020 Definitions", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.03.020"}
