{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.04.040 Licensing No person shall rice who does not have in his or her possession a valid license issued to him or her by the Conservation Department, or who does not have or is not eligible to receive a membership or enrollment card of the Tribe. ( 9-2-81-12 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.04.040 was formerly codified as 303.4", "num": "3.04.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.04|3.04.040", "title": "3.04.040 Licensing", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.04.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.04.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.04.050 Notice and Posting (a) The Conservation Department shall monitor the ripening of wild rice within the reservation and shall give notice 24 hours before opening the first area of the season. Thereafter no notice need be given before opening additional areas. (b) The Conservation Department shall post signs indicating the limits of open areas. ( 9-2-81-12 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.04.050 was formerly codified as 303.5", "num": "3.04.050", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.04|3.04.050", "title": "3.04.050 Notice and Posting", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.04.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.04.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.04.060 Mechanization Prohibited No person shall use any mechanical means to harvest wild rice, nor shall any person operate any boat motor or engine within the rice fields. ( 10-7-81-26 ; 9-2-81-12 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.04.060 was formerly codified as 303.6", "num": "3.04.060", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.04|3.04.060", "title": "3.04.060 Mechanization Prohibited", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.04.060"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.04.070", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.04.070 Forfeitures (a) Any person violating Sections 303.3, 303.4, or 303.6 of this chapter for the first time shall be subject to a forfeiture of not more than $150.00. (b) Any person violating Sections 3.04.030, 3.04.040, or 3.04.060 of this chapter who has been previously found to have violated either Sections 3.04.030, 3.04.040, or 3.04.060 of this chapter or who is subsequently found to have previously violated either Section 3.04.030, 3.04.040, or 3.04.060 of this chapter shall be subject to a forfeiture of not more than $250.00. ( 9-2-81-12 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.04.070 was formerly codified as 303.7", "num": "3.04.070", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.04|3.04.070", "title": "3.04.070 Forfeitures", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.04.070"}
