{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.04.080 Seizure and Forfeiture (a) Any rice harvested in violation of this chapter may be seized by the Conservation Department and ordered forfeited. (b) Any equipment used in violation of this chapter may be seized by the Conservation Department and ordered forfeited. ( 9-2-81-12 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.04.080 was formerly codified as 303.8", "num": "3.04.080", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.04|3.04.080", "title": "3.04.080 Seizure and Forfeiture", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.04.080"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 3.05 Trapping Ordinance 3.05.010 Purpose 3.05.020 Jurisdiction 3.05.030 Sale of Fur 3.05.040 Limitation of Tags 3.05.050 Prohibitions 3.05.060 Penalty", "num": "3.05", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.05", "title": "Chapter 3.05 Trapping Ordinance", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.05.010 Purpose It is the purpose and intent of this ordinance to regulate the taking of fur bearers on the Bad River Reservation. The Tribe believes it is important to provide an opportunity for its trappers to take such animals as are necessary for cultural or economic purposes while still protecting the integrity of the species. The Tribe also believes it is important to provide for a system which protects its members from harassment and interference by non-Indians. ( 12-3-86-119 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.05.010 was formerly codified as 304.1", "num": "3.05.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.05|3.05.010", "title": "3.05.010 Purpose", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.05.020 Jurisdiction Any violation of this ordinance shall be referred to the Bad River Tribal Court. ( 12-3-86-119 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.05.020 was formerly codified as 304.2", "num": "3.05.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.05|3.05.020", "title": "3.05.020 Jurisdiction", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.05.030 Sale of Fur Any furs, either trapped or shot by a Bad River Tribal member on reservation, which shall be sold to an authorized fur dealer or individual shall be tagged with the Bad River registration tag. ( 12-3-86-119 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.05.030 was formerly codified as 304.3", "num": "3.05.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.05|3.05.030", "title": "3.05.030 Sale of Fur", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.05.040 Limitation of Tags Such tribal trapper/hunter who traps or kills certain tribally designated protected species shall be limited to either one or two tags depending on the species. These species shall be established by the Bad River Conservation Department. Additional tags may be distributed if the individual meets the requirements set forth by the Conservation Department. The Tribe designates bobcat and fisher as protected species for 1986-87. ( 12-3-86-119 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.05.040 was formerly codified as 304.4", "num": "3.05.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.05|3.05.040", "title": "3.05.040 Limitation of Tags", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.05.050 Prohibitions No member shall tag or sell any fur pursuant to this system which was not trapped/killed by a tribal member on the reservation. This shall not be construed to prohibit members from trapping/killing game off reservation pursuant to an off reservation system. ( 12-3-86-119 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.05.050 was formerly codified as 304.5", "num": "3.05.050", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.05|3.05.050", "title": "3.05.050 Prohibitions", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.05.060 Penalty (a) A violation of sections 304.3 and 304.4 shall result in a minimum forfeiture of no less than $50.00. (b) A violation of Section 3.05.050 shall result in a forfeiture of no less than $100.00. (c) Community service may be assessed in addition to the penalties set forth in (b) or in lieu of the penalties assessed in (a). (d) Tags for any species including fish may be withheld upon failure to pay the set forfeiture or with flagrant or multiple violations, tags will be withheld. ( 12-3-86-119 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.05.060 was formerly codified as 304.6", "num": "3.05.060", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.05|3.05.060", "title": "3.05.060 Penalty", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.05.060"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 3.06 Tagging 3.06.010 Definitions 3.06.020 Tagging Required 3.06.030 Issuance of Tags 3.06.040 Issuance Fees 3.06.050 Records 3.06.060 Lake Trout 3.06.070 Forfeitures", "num": "3.06", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.06", "title": "Chapter 3.06 Tagging", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.06.010 Definitions (a) \"Office\" means the Rights Protection Office of the Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Tribe of Chippewa Indians. (b) \"Reservation\" means all lands within the exterior boundaries of the Bad River Reservation. (c) \"Warden\" means the Chief Conservation Officer of the Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Tribe of Chippewa Indians or any of his deputies. ( 11-18-82-01 ; 11-5-80-132 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.06.010 was formerly codified as 305.1", "num": "3.06.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.06|3.06.010", "title": "3.06.010 Definitions", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.06.020 Tagging Required No person shall remove from the Reservation any fish or game that does not bear a tag issued in conformity with the procedures established by Sections 305.3 and 305.4 herein. ( 11-18-82-01 ; 11-5-80-132 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.06.020 was formerly codified as 305.2", "num": "3.06.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.06|3.06.020", "title": "3.06.020 Tagging Required", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.06.030 Issuance of Tags (a) Any person authorized by treaty, tribal ordinance, or tribal license to fish, hunt, or trap on Reservation lands may apply to the Warden for the issuance of tags. (b) After inspection of the fish or game the applicant proposes to remove from the Reservation, and upon payment by the applicant of an issuance fee, the Warden shall issue, attach, and lock on each carcass or party thereof proposed for removal, a tag bearing a number and the words \"Bad River Tribe'. (c) No tags shall be issued to any applicant for a number of carcasses or parts thereof greater than the number the applicant is authorized to remove. ( 11-18-82-01 ; 11-5-80-132 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.06.030 was formerly codified as 305.3", "num": "3.06.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.06|3.06.030", "title": "3.06.030 Issuance of Tags", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.06.040 Issuance Fees (a) A schedule of issuance fees shall be compiled by the Office. Fees shall reflect the costs incurred by the Office in procuring and distributing the tags. (b) Persons eligible to receive tags may pre-pay for the number of tags which they are authorized to receive or any portion thereof. The Warden may issue tags to an applicant who has so pre-paid by deducting from the applicant's account the number of tags issued. ( 11-18-82-01 ; 11-5-80-132 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.06.040 was formerly codified as 305.4", "num": "3.06.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.06|3.06.040", "title": "3.06.040 Issuance Fees", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.06.050 Records (a) Upon issuance of a tag, the Warden shall record in a record book the following information: (1) The date of issuance. (2) The name and address of the person to whom issued. (3) The species and a description of the fish or game tagged. (4) The destination of the person to whom issued. (5) The name of the issuing warden. (b) The record book containing the information required by Section 3.06.050(a) shall be available to the public during regular working hours for inspection and duplication. ( 11-18-82-01 ; 11-5-80-132 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.06.050 was formerly codified as 305.5", "num": "3.06.050", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.06|3.06.050", "title": "3.06.050 Records", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.06.060 Lake Trout Any tribal member who, fishing under his rights as a Bad River member, catches lake trout in Lake Superior is required to obtain a tag for each fish, under any procedures specified by this chapter , prior to his transportation of the fish off of the reservation, or his introduction of the fish into off-reservation commerce. ( 11-18-82-01 ; 11-5-80-132 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.06.060 was formerly codified as 305.6", "num": "3.06.060", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.06|3.06.060", "title": "3.06.060 Lake Trout", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.060"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.070", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.06.070 Forfeitures (a) Any person violating Section 3.06.020 or Section 3.06.060 for the first time shall be subject to a forfeiture of not more than $150.00. (b) Any person violating Section 3.06.020 or Section 3.06.060 who has been previously found to have violated the same section or who is subsequently found have previously violated the same section shall be subject to a forfeiture of not more than $250.00. ( 11-18-82-01 ; 11-5-80-132 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.06.070 was formerly codified as 305.7", "num": "3.06.070", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.06|3.06.070", "title": "3.06.070 Forfeitures", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.06.070"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.07", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 3.07 Moose 3.07.010 Prohibitions 3.07.020 Penalty 3.07.030 Effective Date 3.07.040 Sunset", "num": "3.07", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.07", "title": "Chapter 3.07 Moose", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.07"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.07.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.07.010 Prohibitions (a) No member of the Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Tribe of Chippewa Indians may shoot, shoot at, or kill any moose on the Bad River Reservation (Reservation). (b) No member may harass, molest, worry, or cause or permit an animal owned by him or her to harass, molest or worry any moose on the Reservation. Prior Codifications \u00a73.07.010 was formerly codified as 306.01", "num": "3.07.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.07|3.07.010", "title": "3.07.010 Prohibitions", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.07.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.07.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.07.020 Penalty Any member found by the Bad River Tribal Court to have violated Section 3.07.010(a) or (b) may be ordered to forfeit not more than $2,500.00. Prior Codifications \u00a73.07.020 was formerly codified as 306.02", "num": "3.07.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.07|3.07.020", "title": "3.07.020 Penalty", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.07.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.07.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.07.030 Effective Date The chapter is effective as of the date of passage. Prior Codifications \u00a73.07.030 was formerly codified as 306.03", "num": "3.07.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.07|3.07.030", "title": "3.07.030 Effective Date", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.07.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.07.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.07.040 Sunset This chapter shall of no force and effect on and after August 15, 1995, unless renewed by the Tribal Council. Prior Codifications \u00a73.07.040 was formerly codified as 306.04", "num": "3.07.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.07|3.07.040", "title": "3.07.040 Sunset", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.07.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 3.08 Closed Fishing Season 3.08.010 Prohibiting of Fishing 3.08.020 Posting 3.08.030 Penalties 3.08.040 Right to Trial 3.08.050 Game Wardens 3.08.060 Seizure 3.08.070 Forfeiture", "num": "3.08", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.08", "title": "Chapter 3.08 Closed Fishing Season", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.08.010 Prohibiting of Fishing The taking of fish by any means during the spawning season from the waters of the Kakagon Sloughs, Wood Creek, and Bear Trap Creek, by members and non-members, is banned, except for the fish needed by the Fish Hatchery located on the Bad River Reservation and other lawfully authorized personnel in the performance of their duties, i.e. U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service. Prior Codifications \u00a73.08.010 was formerly codified as 310.1", "num": "3.08.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.08|3.08.010", "title": "3.08.010 Prohibiting of Fishing", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.08.020 Posting The exterior boundaries of the Bad River Reservation and any acquired lands outside of the Reservation shall be posted as to the closure set forth in Section 3.08.010. Prior Codifications \u00a73.08.020 was formerly codified as 310.2", "num": "3.08.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.08|3.08.020", "title": "3.08.020 Posting", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.08.030 Penalties (a) Any individual who violates this ordinance and does so for the first time shall be punished by a fine of not more than one hundred dollars ($100.00). (b) An individual who violates this ordinance, who has previously been found guilty of violating this same ordinance, shall be punished by a fine of up to but not more than two hundred fifty dollars ($250.00). Prior Codifications \u00a73.08.030 was formerly codified as 310.3", "num": "3.08.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.08|3.08.030", "title": "3.08.030 Penalties", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.08.040 Right to Trial Any person accused of violating this ordinance shall be entitled to a trial in the Bad River Tribal Court. Prior Codifications \u00a73.08.040 was formerly codified as 310.4", "num": "3.08.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.08|3.08.040", "title": "3.08.040 Right to Trial", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.08.050 Game Wardens This ordinance shall be enforced by Tribal Game Wardens to be appointed by the Tribal Council. Prior Codifications \u00a73.08.050 was formerly codified as 310.5", "num": "3.08.050", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.08|3.08.050", "title": "3.08.050 Game Wardens", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.08.060 Seizure Game Wardens and other appointed officials are hereby authorized to seize and impound weapons, fishing, trapping, and ricing gear and other implements used in such activities as evidence together with any fish, game or rice as found in the possession of a person violating this ordinance in order to utilize such in connection with prosecution. Prior Codifications \u00a73.08.060 was formerly codified as 310.6", "num": "3.08.060", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.08|3.08.060", "title": "3.08.060 Seizure", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.060"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.070", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.08.070 Forfeiture The court may order all impounded weapons, gear, implements and fish, and rice forfeited, as to any individual who does not appear in court at the time required or who is found by the court to have committed a breach of this ordinance. Prior Codifications \u00a73.08.070 was formerly codified as 310.7", "num": "3.08.070", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.08|3.08.070", "title": "3.08.070 Forfeiture", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.08.070"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. Chapter 3.09 Setting of Nets 3.09.010 3.09.020 3.09.030 3.09.040 3.09.050 3.09.060", "num": "3.09", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.09", "title": "Chapter 3.09 Setting of Nets", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.09.010 Any nets set in any river, stream, or other navigable water within the boundaries of the Bad River Reservation shall be sunk so as not to impede navigation. Prior Codifications \u00a73.09.010 was formerly codified as 315.1", "num": "3.09.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.09|3.09.010", "title": "3.09.010", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.09.020 Any net in river, stream, or other navigable water within the boundaries of the Bad River Reservation shall be marked with the name of the owner and the words \"Bad River\" or an abbreviation thereof, indicating the tribal membership of the owner. Such marking shall be of an indelible nature and shall be placed on a red or white buoy, jug or other floating device. Prior Codifications \u00a73.09.020 was formerly codified as 315.2", "num": "3.09.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.09|3.09.020", "title": "3.09.020", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.09.030 Any person who sets a net in any river, stream, or other navigable water within the Bad River Reservation shall check the net and remove all fish therefrom at least once within each twenty-four hour period. Prior Codifications \u00a73.09.030 was formerly codified as 315.3", "num": "3.09.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.09|3.09.030", "title": "3.09.030", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.09.040 Except as provided in Section 3.09.050, no person shall remove fish from the net of another without authorization by the owner of the net. Any owner giving authorization shall so notify the Bad River Conservation Office. Prior Codifications \u00a73.09.040 was formerly codified as 315.4", "num": "3.09.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.09|3.09.040", "title": "3.09.040", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.09.050 Tribal conservation wardens may inspect any net found in any river, stream, or other navigable waters within the Bad River Reservation. Any net which a warden reasonably suspects to be in violation of Section 3.09.010, 3.09.010, or 3.09.010 of this ordinance may be immediately seized, including any fish therein. Prior Codifications \u00a73.09.050 was formerly codified as 315.5", "num": "3.09.050", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.09|3.09.050", "title": "3.09.050", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.09.060 For a first violation of Sections 315.1, 315.2, or 315.3 of this ordinance, a civil forfeiture not to exceed $50.00 may be assessed, and the net used forfeited. For a second violation and any violation subsequent thereto of Sections 315.1, 2 or 3, a civil forfeiture not to exceed $100.00 may be assessed and the net used forfeited. For a violation of Section 3.09.040 of this ordinance a civil forfeiture not to exceed $100.00 may be assessed. For a second violation and any violation subsequent thereto of Section 3.09.040 a civil forfeiture of $200.00 may be assessed. In addition to the forfeiture assessed for a violation of Section 3.09.040, the court may order restitution made to the person whose net was subject to the unauthorized taking. Prior Codifications \u00a73.09.060 was formerly codified as 315.6", "num": "3.09.060", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.09|3.09.060", "title": "3.09.060", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.09.060"}
