{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.13.200 Assistants (a) No person who is not a member of a Chippewa tribe with fishing rights in Lake Superior or who has had his or her on-reservation or off-reservation fishing rights revoked or suspended shall participate in the taking of any treaty protected fishery resource, and no member shall be a party to such taking by a nonmember, except as specifically provided by this section. (b) Members of the immediate family of a tribal member may assist the tribal member, in his or her presence, in the commercial taking of treaty-protected fish in Lake Superior. ( 1-10-07-13 ; 11-5-86-79 ; 3-20-86-11 ; 3-7-84-59 .) Prior Codifications \u00a73.13.200 was formerly codified as 325.20", "num": "3.13.200", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.13|3.13.200", "title": "3.13.200 Assistants", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.13.200"}
