{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.15.120 Backfire Flame Control Gasoline engines must have backfire flame control; exception: not necessary for outboard motors and for engines that are located where there is a free flowing exchange of air (for example, where forced ventilation is not necessary). Prior Codifications \u00a73.15.120 was formerly codified as 327.12", "num": "3.15.120", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.15|3.15.120", "title": "3.15.120 Backfire Flame Control", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.15.120"}
