{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.17.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.17.020 Permits Authorized Upon application to the Conservation Department, a non-member Indian residing on the Reservation who is married to a member or who has a child who is a member and for whose support the non-member is obligated, may be issued a permit allowing the non-member to hunt deer on the reservation, for the consumption of the non-member and the non-member's immediate family. Such permit shall be valid only for the period July 1, through December 31 of the year in which the permit is issued. Prior Codifications \u00a73.17.020 was formerly codified as 331.2", "num": "3.17.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.17|3.17.020", "title": "3.17.020 Permits Authorized", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.17.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.17.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.17.030 Waiver and Consent Required No permit shall be issued under Section 3.17.020 unless the applicant signs a statement irrevocably waiving any objection to the applicability of the Bad River Tribe's civil laws, and to the civil jurisdiction of the Bad River Tribal court over any violation the applicant may be alleged to commit. The applicant shall further affirmatively give his irrevocable consent to the civil jurisdiction of the Tribal Court over any offenses the applicant may be alleged to commit. Prior Codifications \u00a73.17.030 was formerly codified as 331.3", "num": "3.17.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.17|3.17.030", "title": "3.17.030 Waiver and Consent Required", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.17.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.17.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.17.040 Automatic Lapse of Permit Any permit issued under Section 3.17.020 shall automatically cease to have any force and effect upon any of the following conditions: (a) The permittee removes from residence on the reservation. (b) The permittee ceases to have a spouse or child who is a member and for whose support he is obligated. (c) The permittee purports to revoke his waiver or consent as required by Section 3.17.010. Prior Codifications \u00a73.17.040 was formerly codified as 331.4", "num": "3.17.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.17|3.17.040", "title": "3.17.040 Automatic Lapse of Permit", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.17.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.17.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.17.050 Prohibitions (a) No non-member resident Indian shall hunt, fish, trap, or gather on the Reservation without a permit as provided in Section 3.17.020. (b) No non-member Indian shall hunt, fish, trap, or gather after any permit issued to him or her shall have lapsed pursuant to Section 3.17.040. (c) No non-member Indian shall violate any terms of any permit issued to him or her pursuant to Section 3.17.020. (d) No non-member shall make any false representation on his or her application for a permit under Section 3.17.020. Prior Codifications \u00a73.17.050 was formerly codified as 331.5", "num": "3.17.050", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.17|3.17.050", "title": "3.17.050 Prohibitions", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.17.050"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.17.060", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.17.060 Forfeitures For any violation of this chapter , a non-member may be subject to a civil forfeiture not to exceed $500 and revocation of all hunting, fishing, trapping, and gathering privileges. Prior Codifications \u00a73.17.060 was formerly codified as 331.6", "num": "3.17.060", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.17|3.17.060", "title": "3.17.060 Forfeitures", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.17.060"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.17.070", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 3.17.070 Non-Member Assistance The prohibition contained in Section 3.16.040 shall not apply to any non-member resident Indian possessing a permit issued under Section 3.17.020. Prior Codifications \u00a73.17.070 was formerly codified as 331.7", "num": "3.17.070", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|3|3.17|3.17.070", "title": "3.17.070 Non-Member Assistance", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/3.17.070"}
