{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 5.01.090 General Under 25 U.S.C. \u00a7 2703(7) of the IGRA, Class II games may utilize electronic, computer or other technologic aids. At the same time, IGRA strictly prohibits the use of electronic or electromechanical facsimiles of any game of chance without a tribal-state compact or procedures issued by the Secretary of the Interior. Any Gaming System that is determined by the Tribal Gaming Commission not to be Class II may only be operated at the Tribal Gaming Facility pursuant to the terms of a tribal-state compact or Class III gaming procedures. ( 9-21-12 ; 11-29-07-190 ; 11-29-07-189 ; 12-29-04-31 ; 12-29-04-30 ; 12-29-04-29 ; 3-21-03-59 ; 6-19-02-295 ; 9-18-01-157 ; 7-2-01-119B ; 3-01-01-49 ; 1-5-00-369 ; 4-8-98-132 ; 9-6-93-81 ; 10-7-92-154 ; 9-20-91-151 ; 4-1-87-39 ; 6-4-86-34 .) Prior Codifications \u00a75.01.090 was formerly codified as 500.31", "num": "5.01.090", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|5|5.01|B|5.01.090", "title": "5.01.090 General", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.01.090"}
