{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 5.01.100 Definitions For the purposes of this subchapter , the following definitions shall be used. Words in the present tense include the future; the singular includes the plural; and the plural includes the singular. The word \"shall\" is mandatory and the word \"may\" is permissive. Electronic Bingo (Class II) (a) Definitions (1) \"Bingo\" means the game of chance set forth in the IGRA at 25 U.S.C. \u00a7 2703(7)(A)(i), (whether or not electronic, computer, or other technologic aids are used in connection therewith): (A) Which is played for Prizes, including monetary Prizes, with Cards bearing numbers or other designations; (B) In which the holder of the Card covers such numbers or designations when objects, similarly numbered or designated, are drawn or electronically determined; and (C) In which the game is won by the first person covering a previously designated arrangement of numbers or designations on such Cards. (2) \"Card\" means an array of numbers or other designations, presented on paper and/or in electronic form, that is used by a player as a basis to Cover such numbers or other designations drawn or electronically determined in a Bingo game. (3) \"Claim\" means a player's declaration of the right to a Prize under the Rules of Play. (4) \"Classification Determination\" means a formal determination by the Tribal Gaming Commission that a Gaming System is Class II under this Regulation. (5) \"Consideration\" means the player's payment or credit to participate or to continue participating in a game. (6) \"Council\" or \"Tribal Council\" means the seven (7) member committee composed of elected tribal officials authorized to represent the Tribe pursuant to the Tribe's Constitution. (7) \"Cover\" means the process of matching or daubing the numbers or other designations on a Card that correspond to numbers or other designations from a Draw. (8) \"Draw\" means the physical or electronic selection of numbers or other designations from the set of numbers or other designations used to determine winners in a Bingo game. (9) \"Electronic, Computer or Other Technologic Aid\"\" has the meaning set forth in Section 5.01.130(a)(2) of this Regulation. (10) \"Electronic or Electromechanical Facsimile\" has the meaning set forth in Section 5.01.130(a)(3) of this Regulation. (11) \"Game Winning Card\" means a Card on which a Game Winning Pattern has been Covered. There may be more than one Game Winning Card in any Bingo game. (12) \"Game Winning Pattern\" means a specific array of numbers or other designations on a Card that, when Covered on the Card(s), entitles the player(s) to receive the Game Winning Prize. (13) \"Tribal Gaming Commission\" means a Tribally designated entity responsible for Gaming regulation. (14) \"Gaming System\" means all components, including electronic, computer, or other technologic equipment, that function together to aid the play of one or more games of Bingo including any Player Interfaces. (15) \"NIGC\" means the National Indian Gaming Commission. (16) \"NIGC Technical Standards\" means the Technical Standards for Electronic, Computer, or Other Technologic Aids Used in the Play of Class II Games, 25 C.F.R. Part 547. (17) \"Pattern\" means, in the case of a Game Winning Pattern, an array of two or more numbers or other designations on a Card. A Pattern for a Prize Winning Pattern must contain at least one number or other designation on a Card. (18) \"Player Interface\" means any component or components of a Gaming System, including an electronic or technologic aid such as terminals, player stations, handhelds, fixed units, etc. that directly enables player interaction in a game of Bingo. (19) \"Prize\" means anything of material value, including money, which is awarded to a player under the Rules of Play. (20) \"Prize Pool\" means the cumulative amount of contributions paid by participants in one of more games of Bingo, which is used to fund prizes specified in the Rules of Play. (21) \"Prize Winning Card\" means a Card on which a Prize Winning Pattern has been Covered, entitling a player to Claim an interim or consolation Prize under the Rules of Play. There may be more than one Prize Winning Card in any Bingo game. (22) \"Prize Winning Pattern\" means a specific array of numbers or other designations that, when Covered on a Card(s), entitles the player(s) to receive an interim or consolation Prize. (23) \"Random Number Generator (RNG)\" means an electronic or mechanical method for determining numbers or other designations in a game of chance that must meet the applicable standards for randomness set forth in the NIGC Technical Standards or established by the Tribal Gaming Commission. (24) \"Rules of Play\" means the specific rules controlling the play of the subject game of Bingo. (25) \"Server\" means a computer which controls one or more applications or environments within a Gaming System. (26) \"Tribal Gaming Facility\" means the Casino, which is located on the Indian lands of the Tribe operated pursuant to the Tribe's Gaming Ordinance. (27) \"Tribal Gaming Facility Manager (TGFM)\" means the Casino Gaming Manager who operates the gaming facility for the Tribe. ( 9-21-12 ; 11-29-07-190 ; 11-29-07-189 ; 12-29-04-31 ; 12-29-04-30 ; 12-29-04-29 ; 3-21-03-59 ; 6-19-02-295 ; 9-18-01-157 ; 7-2-01-119B ; 3-01-01-49 ; 1-5-00-369 ; 4-8-98-132 ; 9-6-93-81 ; 10-7-92-154 ; 9-20-91-151 ; 4-1-87-39 ; 6-4-86-34 .) Prior Codifications \u00a75.01.100 was formerly codified as 500.32", "num": "5.01.100", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|5|5.01|B|5.01.100", "title": "5.01.100 Definitions", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.01.100"}
