{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 5.01.110 Classification Procedure (a) Application Process (1) Only a duly authorized representative of the GM may apply for a Classification Determination under this Regulation. (2) The GM may apply for a Classification Determination at any time, but must do so before offering a new Gaming System for play under the following circumstances: (A The GM wishes to install a new Gaming System that is not the subject of an existing Classification Determination and is not otherwise permitted as a Class III game; or (B) The GM wishes to introduce a material modification to a previously approved Gaming System, including a Gaming system approved before the effective date of this Regulation. (C) Although not required, the GM also may apply for a Classification Determination under this Regulation for a Gaming System approved by the Tribal Gaming Commission before the effective date of this Regulation. (b) Application Submission Requirements (1) To obtain a Classification Determination, the GM must submit an application to the Tribal Gaming Commission, which consists of the following documentation and information: (A) Request for a Classification Determination; (B) Certification by the vendor of the Gaming System that the Gaming System to be placed in the Tribal Gaming Facility: (i) Is within the criteria for a Class II game of Bingo under IGRA and this Regulation; (ii) Complies in all respects with the specifications and standards set forth in the application ; and (iii) Complies with any applicable regulations concerning such Gaming System. (C) A legal opinion that concludes that the Gaming System is a Class II game of Bingo under the IGRA played using a permitted electronic, computer or other technologic aids; (D) GM's statement that, to the best of its knowledge and belief, the subject Gaming System meets the standards in these Regulations; [optional] (E) Designation of a point of contact authorized to provide additional information if required; (F) Designation from the vendor of whether and where the Gaming System is already in play; (G) Complete written description from the vendor of the Gaming System, including the operational characteristics and Rules of Play; (H) Complete description of the method used for accepting Consideration from players, paying or distributing Prizes to winners, determining, retaining or paying any amounts to the operator or vendor from the Consideration or any other source, and the awarding or funding of Prize Pools; (I) Copy of any of the vendor's sales or promotional literature for the Gaming System; [Optional] (J) For Gaming Systems already in play at the Tribal Gaming Facility, a complete list of the serial numbers or other identifiers of each Player Interface or other device used in the play of the Gaming System; (K) Report of laboratory test(s), which must be addressed to the Tribal Gaming Commission, which were conducted that validate that the Gaming System meets the requirements of Sections B(1)(b)(ii) and (iii) of this Article, as well as the requirements of the NIGC Technical Standards found at 25 C.F.R. Part 547; (L) Copies of any court or administrative decisions or other materials, supplied by the Gaming System vendor, which address the classification of the proposed Gaming System, if any; (c) Submission of Additional Information Upon request of the Tribal Gaming Commission, the GM may be required to provide any further information or clarification the Tribal Gaming Commission deems necessary to make a Classification Determination. ( 9-21-12 ; 11-29-07-190 ; 11-29-07-189 ; 12-29-04-31 ; 12-29-04-30 ; 12-29-04-29 ; 3-21-03-59 ; 6-19-02-295 ; 9-18-01-157 ; 7-2-01-119B ; 3-01-01-49 ; 1-5-00-369 ; 4-8-98-132 ; 9-6-93-81 ; 10-7-92-154 ; 9-20-91-151 ; 4-1-87-39 ; 6-4-86-34 .) Prior Codifications \u00a75.01.110 was formerly codified as 500.33", "num": "5.01.110", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|5|5.01|B|5.01.110", "title": "5.01.110 Classification Procedure", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.01.110"}
