{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 5.01.140 Classification Decisions (a) Issuance of a Written Classification Determination If the Tribal Gaming Commission determines that the Gaming System meets the criteria in Article 6 above, it shall issue a written Classification Determination and shall provide copies of such Classification Determination to the Tribal Council and the GM. (b) Issuance of an Unfavorable Determination If the Tribal Gaming Commission determines that the Gaming System does not meet one or more of the criteria in Article 6 above, it shall issue a written decision specifically addressing the reasons for its determination and shall provide copies of such decision to the Tribal Council and the GM. (c) Finality of the Decision If the Tribal Gaming Commission determines that a Gaming System is not Class II for any reason, the decision of the Tribal Gaming Commission will be final and binding. The Tribal Gaming Commission may, in its discretion, allow a request for reconsideration upon a showing of new factual evidence or legal support. ( 9-21-12 ; 11-29-07-190 ; 11-29-07-189 ; 12-29-04-31 ; 12-29-04-30 ; 12-29-04-29 ; 3-21-03-59 ; 6-19-02-295 ; 9-18-01-157 ; 7-2-01-119B ; 3-01-01-49 ; 1-5-00-369 ; 4-8-98-132 ; 9-6-93-81 ; 10-7-92-154 ; 9-20-91-151 ; 4-1-87-39 ; 6-4-86-34 .) Prior Codifications \u00a75.01.140 was formerly codified as 500.36", "num": "5.01.140", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|5|5.01|B|5.01.140", "title": "5.01.140 Classification Decisions", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.01.140"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.01.150", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 5.01.150 Installation of Gaming Systems (a) Confirmation of Specifications The Tribal Gaming Commission requires the manufacturer or distributor of Gaming Systems intended for use in this jurisdiction to certify, in writing, that prior to delivery to the Tribe, each Gaming System: (1) Conforms precisely to the exact specifications of the system prototype tested and approved by the test laboratory. (2) Can be tested using one or more unique signatures, checksum values or similar technology for the operating programs used with the electronic computer, or other technologic aid. (3) Operates and plays in accordance with the NIGC Technical Standards, this Regulation and all other applicable Tribal Gaming Commission regulations. (b) Integrity of Seals Upon delivery of a Gaming System to the Tribal Gaming Facility, no one will break the seal of any delivery container, nor will any system be removed from the shipping container without the physical presence and authorization of a Tribal Gaming Commission official. (c) Use of Approved Locks The GM shall replace Player Interface locks with locks approved for use by the Tribal Gaming Commission. (d) System Modifications The GM shall develop policies and procedures to be approved by the Tribal Gaming Commission for installing, accessing, maintaining, repairing, and configuring systems in the same manner as set forth in Tribal Gaming Commission regulations. (e) Delivery of Gaming Systems At least ten (10) calendar days prior to shipping and delivery of a Gaming System, each manufacturer or distributor shall report in writing to the Tribal Gaming Commission the following information for each Player Interface to be used as part of the Gaming System: (1) The type of Player Interface (i.e. hand-held or fixed-base). (2) The Player Interface serial number. (3) The manufacturer of the Player Interface. (4) The vendor from whom the Player Interface was acquired, the means by which the Player Interface will be transported into the state, and the name and street address of any common carrier or other person transporting the Player Interface. (5) The date of shipping and anticipated delivery date. (f) Notice of New or Upgraded Software The Tribal Gaming Commission shall be notified by the GM of any subsequent purchases of any new or upgraded program software within ten (10) calendar days. ( 9-21-12 ; 11-29-07-190 ; 11-29-07-189 ; 12-29-04-31 ; 12-29-04-30 ; 12-29-04-29 ; 3-21-03-59 ; 6-19-02-295 ; 9-18-01-157 ; 7-2-01-119B ; 3-01-01-49 ; 1-5-00-369 ; 4-8-98-132 ; 9-6-93-81 ; 10-7-92-154 ; 9-20-91-151 ; 4-1-87-39 ; 6-4-86-34 .) Prior Codifications \u00a75.01.150 was formerly codified as 500.37", "num": "5.01.150", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|5|5.01|B|5.01.150", "title": "5.01.150 Installation of Gaming Systems", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.01.150"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.01.160", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 5.01.160 Labeling of Approved Gaming Systems (a) Serial Numbers Once a Gaming System has been determined to be Class II, the GM will provide a serial number and description of each Player Interface to the Tribal Gaming Commission. (b) Requirement for Seals or Labels The Tribal Gaming Commission shall affix a seal or a label on each of the internal components of each Player Interface to indicate proper determination. The seal or other label will be visible when the Player Interface door is open and will show the version number(s) or other unique identifier(s), as documented by the testing laboratory. The seal or other label will be promptly removed from the Player Interface when the version number(s) of the software operated thereon are changed and a new seal or other label affixed showing the versions of the software in use; provided the new version(s) meet the standards established in this Regulation. ( 9-21-12 ; 11-29-07-190 ; 11-29-07-189 ; 12-29-04-31 ; 12-29-04-30 ; 12-29-04-29 ; 3-21-03-59 ; 6-19-02-295 ; 9-18-01-157 ; 7-2-01-119B ; 3-01-01-49 ; 1-5-00-369 ; 4-8-98-132 ; 9-6-93-81 ; 10-7-92-154 ; 9-20-91-151 ; 4-1-87-39 ; 6-4-86-34 .) Prior Codifications \u00a75.01.160 was formerly codified as 500.38", "num": "5.01.160", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|5|5.01|B|5.01.160", "title": "5.01.160 Labeling of Approved Gaming Systems", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.01.160"}
