{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 5.05.010 Annual Operating Budget (a) Bingo, raffle, and other Class II gaming conducted at the locale at which Bingo is played shall be carried out in accordance with the annual operating budget adopted for that purpose. Such budget shall detail the operational expenses of the operation and shall be prepared by the Tribal Bingo Manager and presented for approval by the Tribal Council at least one month before the commencement of the budget year. The budget year shall begin January 1 of each year. (b) No expense may be incurred by the Tribal Bingo Manager except as provided for an in conformity with the annual operating budget. (c) The Tribal Council may, as circumstances warrant, amend the annual operating budget during the course of the year. ( 9-21-12 ; 11-29-07-190 ; 11-29-07-189 ; 12-29-04-31 ; 12-29-04-30 ; 12-29-04-29 ; 3-21-03-59 ; 6-19-02-295 ; 9-18-01-157 ; 7-2-01-119B ; 3-01-01-49 ; 1-5-00-369 ; 4-8-98-132 ; 9-6-93-81 ; 10-7-92-154 ; 9-20-91-151 ; 4-1-87-39 ; 6-4-86-34 .) Prior Codifications \u00a75.05.010 was formerly codified as 504.1", "num": "5.05.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|5|5.05|5.05.010", "title": "5.05.010 Annual Operating Budget", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.05.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.05.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 5.05.020 Monthly Financial Report The Tribal Bingo Manager shall prepare, sign, and submit to the Tribal Council a monthly financial report which shall include the following information for the preceding month: (a) The names of all persons employed in the conduct of bingo, raffles, and other associated Class II gaming; (b) The number and dates of all bingo occasions and raffles; (c) An itemized statement of gross receipts from all bingo occasions and other Class II gaming; (d) An itemized list of all expenditures; (e) A statement showing the balance in the bingo account; and (f) An itemized list of transfers from the bingo account to other tribal accounts for administration, government and program expenditures. ( 9-21-12 ; 11-29-07-190 ; 11-29-07-189 ; 12-29-04-31 ; 12-29-04-30 ; 12-29-04-29 ; 3-21-03-59 ; 6-19-02-295 ; 9-18-01-157 ; 7-2-01-119B ; 3-01-01-49 ; 1-5-00-369 ; 4-8-98-132 ; 9-6-93-81 ; 10-7-92-154 ; 9-20-91-151 ; 4-1-87-39 ; 6-4-86-34 .) Prior Codifications \u00a75.05.020 was formerly codified as 504.2", "num": "5.05.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|5|5.05|5.05.020", "title": "5.05.020 Monthly Financial Report", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.05.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.05.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 5.05.030 Bingo Account The Tribal Accounting Office shall create a special account into which bingo, raffle and other Class II gaming receipts shall be deposited. Bingo, raffle, and associated Class II gaming receipts shall be deposited within three days of the Bingo or Raffle. Gross receipts derived from the conduct of bingo, raffles, and other Class II gaming shall not be commingled with any other tribal funds. Transfers from on the bingo account shall only be for one of the following purposes: (a) The payment of reasonable and necessary expenses incurred in connection with the conduct of bingo or raffles in conformity with the annual operating budget including the payment of any assessment under 25 U.S.C. \u00a72717. ( 9-21-12 ; 11-29-07-190 ; 11-29-07-189 ; 12-29-04-31 ; 12-29-04-30 ; 12-29-04-29 ; 3-21-03-59 ; 6-19-02-295 ; 9-18-01-157 ; 7-2-01-119B ; 3-01-01-49 ; 1-5-00-369 ; 4-8-98-132 ; 9-6-93-81 ; 10-7-92-154 ; 9-20-91-151 ; 4-1-87-39 ; 6-4-86-34 .) Prior Codifications \u00a75.05.030 was formerly codified as 504.3", "num": "5.05.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|5|5.05|5.05.030", "title": "5.05.030 Bingo Account", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.05.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.05.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 5.05.040 Audit (a) The bingo, raffle, and other Class II gaming operations shall be subject to an annual outside audit. (b) Included in such annual outside audit shall be all contracts for supplies, services, or concessions for a contract amount in excess of $25,000 annually, except contracts for professional legal or accounting services, related to bingo, raffle, and other class II gaming. ( 9-21-12 ; 11-29-07-190 ; 11-29-07-189 ; 12-29-04-31 ; 12-29-04-30 ; 12-29-04-29 ; 3-21-03-59 ; 6-19-02-295 ; 9-18-01-157 ; 7-2-01-119B ; 3-01-01-49 ; 1-5-00-369 ; 4-8-98-132 ; 9-6-93-81 ; 10-7-92-154 ; 9-20-91-151 ; 4-1-87-39 ; 6-4-86-34 .) Prior Codifications \u00a75.05.040 was formerly codified as 504.4", "num": "5.05.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|5|5.05|5.05.040", "title": "5.05.040 Audit", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.05.040"}
