{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 5.06.060 Class III Gaming - Finances and Accounting (a) The chief management official of the Class III gaming operation shall submit to the Tribal Council a monthly financial report which shall include the following information for the preceding month (b) The Tribal Accounting Office shall create a special account into which Class III receipts shall be deposited. Class III receipts shall not be commingled with any other tribal funds. Checks drawn on the Class III account shall be only be for the following purposes (c) Class III gaming operations shall be subject to an annual outside audit which shall include all contracts for supplies, services, or concessions for a contract amount in excess of $25,000 annually, except for professional legal or accounting services, related to Class III gaming. ( 9-21-12 ; 11-29-07-190 ; 11-29-07-189 ; 12-29-04-31 ; 12-29-04-30 ; 12-29-04-29 ; 3-21-03-59 ; 6-19-02-295 ; 9-18-01-157 ; 7-2-01-119B ; 3-01-01-49 ; 1-5-00-369 ; 4-8-98-132 ; 9-6-93-81 ; 10-7-92-154 ; 9-20-91-151 ; 4-1-87-39 ; 6-4-86-34 .) Prior Codifications \u00a75.06.060 was formerly codified as 505.6", "num": "5.06.060", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|5|5.06|5.06.060", "title": "5.06.060 Class III Gaming - Finances and Accounting", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.06.060"}
