{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 5.08.040 Use of Gaming Revenue (a) Net revenues from Class II and III gaming shall be used only for the following purposes: to fund tribal government operations and programs, provide for the general welfare of the Tribe and its members, promote tribal economic development, donate to charitable organizations, or help fund operations of local government agencies. (b) If the Tribe elects to make per capita payments to tribal members, it shall authorize such payments only upon approval of a plan submitted to the Secretary of the Interior under 25 U.S.C. subsection 2710(b)(3). ( 9-21-12 ; 11-29-07-190 ; 11-29-07-189 ; 12-29-04-31 ; 12-29-04-30 ; 12-29-04-29 ; 3-21-03-59 ; 6-19-02-295 ; 9-18-01-157 ; 7-2-01-119B ; 3-01-01-49 ; 1-5-00-369 ; 4-8-98-132 ; 9-6-93-81 ; 10-7-92-154 ; 9-20-91-151 ; 4-1-87-39 ; 6-4-86-34 .) Prior Codifications \u00a75.08.040 was formerly codified as 550.4", "num": "5.08.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|5|5.08|5.08.040", "title": "5.08.040 Use of Gaming Revenue", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/5.08.040"}
