{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/9.01.010", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 9.01.010 Purpose The purpose of this ordinance is to help provide employment for tribal members living on or near the reservation who may have skills as laborers, heavy machine operators or in other construction areas. Often times there are contracts given out for road, bridge and other types of construction in this area. The idea is to allow for our members participate in such jobs to enable them to be employed and to instill pride in their work on or near the reservation. ( 10-3-86-75 .) Prior Codifications \u00a79.01.010 was formerly codified as 901.1", "num": "9.01.010", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|9|9.01|9.01.010", "title": "9.01.010 Purpose", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/9.01.010"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/9.01.020", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 9.01.020 Definitions (a) \"Tribe\" means the Bad River Band of Lake Superior Tribe of Chippewa Indians. (b) \"Member\" means any person who is a member of the Bad River Band of Lake Superior Tribe of Chippewa Indians. (c) \"Reservation\" refers to all lands and roads within the exterior boundaries of the reservation. (d) \"Contract or subcontract\" refers to any individual, partnership or company who has been awarded a contract or subcontract to do road, bridge or other work on the reservation. (e) \"Tribal Personnel Officer\" refers to that person who is in charge of the Personnel Office. ( 10-3-86-75 .) Prior Codifications \u00a79.01.020 was formerly codified as 901.2", "num": "9.01.020", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|9|9.01|9.01.020", "title": "9.01.020 Definitions", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/9.01.020"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/9.01.030", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 9.01.030 Prohibition (a) No contractor or subcontractor who has been contracted to do road, bridge, or other work on the reservation shall hire any additional persons needed for the job who is not a member of the Tribe unless there is no qualified member of the Tribe able to perform such job or jobs. (b) No contractor or subcontractor shall be deemed to have complied with subsection (a) above unless (1) they have a statement from the Tribal Personnel Officer stating that they have worked with the Personnel Office and (2) the statement sets forth whether or not there are qualified members of the Tribe to perform the job. ( 10-3-86-75 .) Prior Codifications \u00a79.01.030 was formerly codified as 901.3", "num": "9.01.030", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|9|9.01|9.01.030", "title": "9.01.030 Prohibition", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/9.01.030"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/9.01.040", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 9.01.040 Penalties/Forfeitures Violation of Section 9.01.030 of this ordinance shall be subject to the following: (a) Forfeiture not to exceed $500.00, or (b) Recession of the contract if possible, or (c) Barred from receiving future contracts. ( 10-3-86-75 .) Prior Codifications \u00a79.01.040 was formerly codified as 901.4", "num": "9.01.040", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|9|9.01|9.01.040", "title": "9.01.040 Penalties/Forfeitures", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/9.01.040"}
{"index": {"_id": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/9.01.050", "_type": "page"}}
{"body": "Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code. 9.01.050 Violation All violations shall be tried in Tribal or Federal Court. ( 10-3-86-75 .) Prior Codifications \u00a79.01.050 was formerly codified as 901.5", "num": "9.01.050", "path": "library|Bad River Band of the Lake Superior Chippewa Indians Tribal Code|9|9.01|9.01.050", "title": "9.01.050 Violation", "url": "/us/nsn/badriver/council/code/9.01.050"}
